{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":152,"text":"Let me start by asking you a\nquestion, just with a show of hands:"},{"time":3101,"text":"Who has an iPhone?"},{"time":5236,"text":"Who has an Android phone?"},{"time":8326,"text":"Who has a Blackberry?"},{"time":10394,"text":"Who will admit in public to having a Blackberry?"},{"time":12768,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":15351,"text":"And let me guess, how many of you,"},{"time":17439,"text":"when you arrived here, like me, went and bought"},{"time":19447,"text":"a pay-as-you-go SIM card? Yeah?"},{"time":23237,"text":"I'll bet you didn't even know"},{"time":24637,"text":"you're using African technology."},{"time":26615,"text":"Pay-as-you-go was a technology, or an idea,"},{"time":28898,"text":"pioneered in Africa by a company called Vodacom"},{"time":31968,"text":"a good 15 years ago,"},{"time":34371,"text":"and now, like franchising,"},{"time":36916,"text":"pay-as-you-go is one of the most dominant forces"},{"time":39199,"text":"of economic activity in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41776,"text":"So I'm going to talk about innovation in Africa,"},{"time":43668,"text":"which I think is the purest form,"},{"time":45738,"text":"innovation out of necessity."},{"time":47746,"text":"But first, I'm going to ask you some other questions."},{"time":50208,"text":"You don't have to put your hands up."},{"time":51843,"text":"These are rhetorical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54475,"text":"Why did Nikola Tesla have to invent"},{"time":56745,"text":"the alternating current that powers the lights"},{"time":58746,"text":"in this building or the city that we're in?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":61277,"text":"Why did Henry Ford have to\ninvent the production line"},{"time":63965,"text":"to produce these Fords that came in anything"},{"time":66582,"text":"as long as they were black?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68043,"text":"And why did Eric Merrifield\nhave to invent the dolos?"},{"time":72822,"text":"Blank stares. That is what a dolos looks like,"},{"time":75420,"text":"and in the background, you can see Robben Island."},{"time":78241,"text":"This is a small dolos, and Eric Merrifield"},{"time":82290,"text":"is the most famous inventor you've never heard of."},{"time":85053,"text":"In 1963, a storm ripped up the harbor"},{"time":89273,"text":"in a small South African town called East London,"},{"time":91645,"text":"and while he was watching his kids playing"},{"time":94688,"text":"with toys made from oxen bones called dolosse,"},{"time":97234,"text":"he had the idea for this."},{"time":98856,"text":"It's a bit like a huge jumping jack,"},{"time":101073,"text":"and they have used this in every harbor in the world"},{"time":104515,"text":"as a breakwater."},{"time":106135,"text":"The global shipping economy would not be possible"},{"time":109324,"text":"without African technology like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112224,"text":"So whenever you talk about Africa,"},{"time":115973,"text":"you have to put up this picture\nof the world from space,"},{"time":118900,"text":"and people go, \"Look, it's the Dark Continent.\""},{"time":122727,"text":"Actually, it isn't."},{"time":124386,"text":"What it is is a map of innovation."},{"time":126415,"text":"And it's really easy to see\nwhere innovation's going on."},{"time":129900,"text":"All the places with lots of electricity, it isn't."},{"time":133960,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":136987,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":141520,"text":"And the reason it isn't is because everybody's"},{"time":143970,"text":"watching television or playing Angry Birds."},{"time":147155,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150624,"text":"So where it's happening is in Africa."},{"time":153828,"text":"Now, this is real innovation,"},{"time":155646,"text":"not the way people have expropriated the word"},{"time":158801,"text":"to talk about launching new products."},{"time":160994,"text":"This is real innovation, and I\ndefine it as problem-solving."},{"time":164751,"text":"People are solving real problems in Africa."},{"time":167315,"text":"Why? Because we have to."},{"time":169581,"text":"Because we have real problems."},{"time":171314,"text":"And when we solve real problems for people,"},{"time":173910,"text":"we solve them for the rest of the world"},{"time":176307,"text":"at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178411,"text":"So in California, everybody's really excited"},{"time":181746,"text":"about a little square of plastic\nthat you plug into a phone"},{"time":184752,"text":"and you can swipe your credit card,"},{"time":186443,"text":"and people say, \"We've liberated the credit card"},{"time":189322,"text":"from the point of sale terminal.\""},{"time":191996,"text":"Fantastic. Why do you even need a credit card?"},{"time":195410,"text":"In Africa, we've been doing that for years,"},{"time":198758,"text":"and we've been doing it on phones like this."},{"time":200760,"text":"This is a picture I took at a place called Kitengela,"},{"time":203294,"text":"about an hour south of Nairobi,"},{"time":205243,"text":"and the thing that's so remarkable\nabout the payment system"},{"time":208123,"text":"that's been pioneered in Africa called M-Pesa"},{"time":210325,"text":"is that it works on phones like this."},{"time":213069,"text":"It works on every single phone possible,"},{"time":216835,"text":"because it uses SMS."},{"time":218653,"text":"You can pay bills with it, \nyou can buy your groceries,"},{"time":221551,"text":"you can pay your kids' school fees,"},{"time":223549,"text":"and I'm told you can even bribe customs officials."},{"time":227582,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":229063,"text":"Something like 25 million dollars a day"},{"time":232055,"text":"is transacted through M-Pesa."},{"time":234226,"text":"Forty percent of Kenya's GDP"},{"time":236537,"text":"moves through M-Pesa using phones like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239738,"text":"And you think this is just a feature phone."},{"time":241828,"text":"Actually it's the smartphone of Africa."},{"time":244900,"text":"It's also a radio, and it's also a torch,"},{"time":247359,"text":"and more than anything else,"},{"time":248771,"text":"it has really superb battery life."},{"time":251539,"text":"Why? Because that's what we need."},{"time":253641,"text":"We have really severe energy problems in Africa."},{"time":257054,"text":"By the way, you can update Facebook"},{"time":258599,"text":"and send Gmail from a phone like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262272,"text":"So we have found a way to use"},{"time":264852,"text":"the available technology to send money via M-Pesa,"},{"time":267745,"text":"which is a bit like a check system"},{"time":269766,"text":"for the mobile age."},{"time":272008,"text":"I come from Johannesburg, which is a mining town."},{"time":274630,"text":"It's built on gold."},{"time":276094,"text":"This is a picture I Instagrammed earlier."},{"time":278383,"text":"And the difference today is that \nthe gold of today is mobile."},{"time":283748,"text":"If you think about the railroad system\nin North America and how that worked,"},{"time":287991,"text":"first came the infrastructure,"},{"time":289873,"text":"then came the industry around it, the brothels --"},{"time":293153,"text":"it's a bit like the Internet today, right? â€”"},{"time":295145,"text":"and everything else that worked with it:"},{"time":297613,"text":"bars, saloons, etc."},{"time":299680,"text":"The gold of today is mobile,"},{"time":301898,"text":"and mobile is the enabler\nthat makes all of this possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304919,"text":"So what are some of the\nthings that you can do with it?"},{"time":306945,"text":"Well, this is by a guy called\nBright Simons from Ghana,"},{"time":310531,"text":"and what you do is you take medication,"},{"time":312945,"text":"something that some people might\nspend their entire month's salary on,"},{"time":316183,"text":"and you scratch off the code,"},{"time":318948,"text":"and you send that to an SMS number,"},{"time":320890,"text":"and it tells you if that is legitimate"},{"time":322885,"text":"or if it's expired."},{"time":324675,"text":"Really simple, really effective, really life-saving."},{"time":328244,"text":"In Kenya, there's a service called iCow,"},{"time":330433,"text":"which just sends you really important information"},{"time":333372,"text":"about how to look after your dairy."},{"time":335250,"text":"The dairy business in Kenya"},{"time":336791,"text":"is a $463 million business,"},{"time":339597,"text":"and the difference between a subsistence farmer"},{"time":342214,"text":"and an abundance farmer"},{"time":343911,"text":"is only a couple of liters of milk a day."},{"time":346285,"text":"And if you can do that,\nyou can rise out of poverty."},{"time":349305,"text":"Really simple, using a basic phone."},{"time":353276,"text":"If you don't have electricity, no problem!"},{"time":356061,"text":"We'll just make it out of old bicycle parts"},{"time":358022,"text":"using a windmill, as William Kamkwamba did."},{"time":360506,"text":"There's another great African that you've heard"},{"time":362586,"text":"that's busy disrupting the\nautomobile industry in the world."},{"time":366318,"text":"He's also finding a way to reinvent solar power"},{"time":369077,"text":"and the electricity industry in North America,"},{"time":371848,"text":"and if he's lucky, he'll get us to Mars,"},{"time":374931,"text":"hopefully in my lifetime."},{"time":376796,"text":"He comes from Pretoria, the capital of [South Africa],"},{"time":379879,"text":"about 50 kilometers from where I live."},{"time":382815,"text":"So back to Joburg, which is sometimes called Egoli,"},{"time":386397,"text":"which means City of Gold."},{"time":388546,"text":"And not only is mobile the gold of today,"},{"time":392557,"text":"I don't believe that the gold is under the ground."},{"time":394927,"text":"I believe we are the gold."},{"time":396659,"text":"Like you've heard the other economists say,"},{"time":399003,"text":"we are at the point where China was"},{"time":401035,"text":"when its boom years began,"},{"time":403468,"text":"and that's where we're going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404838,"text":"So, you hear the West talk\nabout innovation at the edge."},{"time":409826,"text":"Well, of course it's happening at the edge,"},{"time":411735,"text":"because in the middle,\neverybody's updating Facebook,"},{"time":414732,"text":"or worse still, they're trying to understand"},{"time":416731,"text":"Facebook's privacy settings."},{"time":418858,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":420762,"text":"This is not that catchy catchphrase."},{"time":423308,"text":"This is innovation over the edge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427210,"text":"So, people like to call Africa a mobile-first continent,"},{"time":432176,"text":"but actually it's mobile-only,"},{"time":434850,"text":"so while everybody else is doing all of those things,"},{"time":438495,"text":"we're solving the world's problems."},{"time":439835,"text":"So there's only one thing left to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442158,"text":"[\"You're welcome\"] (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444638,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}